did.unittitle: Kane-Greenberg collection of progressive proof prints

accessrestrict.head: Access to Collection
accessrestrict.p: Collection is open for research; access requires at least 24 hours advance notice.

relatedmaterial.head: Related Materials at The New-York Historical Society
relatedmaterial.p: The Kane-Greenberg Collection of Progressive Proof Prints spans the period from ca. 1890 to ca. 1930 and contains progressive chromolithograph proof books for cigar box labels. These proofs were used to check color quality. Brands from most of the major cigar companies of the time period are represented in the collection. The collection provides a wealth of material for studying the various American advertising themes and iconographic motifs used in the promotion and marketing of a single product. The books are arranged by the letter and number codes printed on them by Consolidated.

custodhist.head: Provenance
custodhist.p: Gift of Raymond Kane, Stanley Greenberg, Neil Greenberg, and Morris Greenberg, 1983.

arrangement.head: Arrangement Note
arrangement.p: Proof books are filed alphabetically by letter, then by number. Books with no letter markings are filed after those with letters. Some proof books are filed in small portfolios, which are housed together, in numerical order. Proof books with no markings are filed at the end of the collection. Cigar brands are noted when apparent.

arrangement.head: Organization of the Collection
arrangement.p:
This collection is organized into series:
Series I: "A" Numbers
Series II: "C" Numbers
Series III: "K" Numbers
Series IV: "M" Numbers"
Series V: Books With Numbers and No Letters
Series VI: Books With No Markings
Series VII: Portfolios
Series VIII: Oversize Materials
